1. Why Go fits what you’ve been exploring

Go (game)

Go is almost pure invariant + delta thinking.

Key ideas in Go:

concept	meaning
influence	invisible structure shaping the board
territory	stable regions (anchors)
liberties	degrees of freedom
sente	initiative / rhythm of play
shape	efficient local structure

Players learn to spot stable shapes (constants) and changes around them (deltas). Exactly the hunter-vision idea you described.

Many top Go players describe it as feeling the flow of the board, not calculating every move.

