2. Why bridges are similar

Bridge engineering is the same principle in physical form.

A bridge is about balancing forces around invariants:

invariant	role
gravity	constant downward force
tension	cables pulling
compression	beams pushing
resonance	vibration stability

Great bridge designs find the simplest stable structure that channels forces efficiently.

Examples include:
	•	suspension bridges
	•	arch bridges
	•	truss bridges

Each is basically a geometry of equilibrium.

