4. A cool historical connection

One of the most famous bridges in math and physics is the Königsberg bridge problem, which led to graph theory through the work of Leonhard Euler.

That single puzzle eventually led to:
	•	network theory
	•	computer science
	•	internet routing
	•	social network analysis

So studying bridges literally helped create modern mathematics.

